# PR 6 fixture: raw triple-quoted string literals.
# Backslash is literal (no escape processing); closing run must
# match the opening length.  ASCII-only -- UTF-8 multi-byte emission
# for hex escapes is PR 7.  Embedded `"` runs inside the body are
# intentionally avoided here: the Python reference has a quirk where
# a non-cleared delim accumulator under-consumes the closing run
# when a shorter `"` run precedes it.  The port mirrors the quirk
# byte-for-byte; the fixture stays on the clean side of it.
"""hello"""
"""back\nslash"""
"""line1
line2"""
"""""hi"""""
